The unit was taken off the grid in September for maintenance after a continuous run of 474 days. CAPE TOWN - Unit 1 of the Koeberg nuclear power station has been reconnected to the grid following planned maintenance.The unit was taken off the grid in September for refuelling and maintenance after a continuous run of 474 days.Eskom spokesperson Khulu Phasiwe says unit 1 is currently operating at a 30% capacity during final start-up tests. It was connected back to the grid at about 3am this morning and it s now going to add just over 900MW into the grid. This will further strengthen the power system as we head into the holiday season. 